yoffs|2012\u201313]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Pallacanestro Varese|Cimberio Varese]]\n| 12 || 1 || 14.8 || 5.8 || 50.0 || 33.3 || 77.8 || 3.4 || 0.7 || 0,0 || 0.8 || 0.8\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| Career\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n| 12 || 1 || 14.8 || 5.8 || 50.0 || 33.3 || 77.8 || 3.4 || 0.7 || 0,0 || 0.8 || 0.8\n{{end}}\n\n==Honours==\n===Individual===\n*'''[[Lega Basket Serie A|Serie A]]'''\n**'''[[Lega Basket Serie A awards#Best Player Under 22|Best Player Under 22]]:''' 2012, 2013\n*'''[[Lega Basket All Star Game]]'''\n**'''Participant:''' 2012\u20132015\n**'''[[Lega Basket All Star Game#Slam dunk contest|Slam dunk contest]] winner:''' 2014\n* [[Premio Reverberi]]: 2015 (best player)\n\n===Team===\n====International====\n*'''[[FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|European Under-20 Championship]]'''\n**[[2011 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|2011 Bilbao]] {{silver medal}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150620062349/http://www.pallacanestroreggiana.it/pagina.php?id=13&n=TEAM&player=POL-ACH-91&year=2014 Pallacanestro Reggiana profile] Retrieved on 16 June 2015.\n* [http://195.56.77.208/player/POL-ACH-91/ Lega Basket Serie A profile] Retrieved 29 June 2015 {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://archive.fiba.com/pages/eng/fa/p/rpp//q/Achille%20Polonara/pid//_//players.html FIBA profile] Retrieved on 16 June 2015.\n* [http://basketball.realgm.com/player/Achille-Polonara/Summary/25898 Real GM profile] Retrieved on 16 June 2015.\n\n{{Saski Baskonia current roster}}\n{{Dinamo Sassari 2018\u201319 FIBA Europe Cup champions}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Polonara, Achille}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dinamo Sassari players]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriate basketball people in Spain]]\n[[Category:Italian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Lega Basket Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Liga ACB players]]\n[[Category:Pallacanestro Reggiana players]]\n[[Category:Pallacanestro Varese players]]\n[[Category:Power forwards (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Saski Baskonia players]]\n[[Category:Small forwards]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Ancona]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Marche]]\n[[Category:Teramo Basket players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name         = Achille Polonara\n| image        = Achille Polonara 2.jpg\n| image_size   = 150px\n| caption      = Polonara playing for Cimberio Varese\n| position     = [[Power forward (basketball)|Power forward]] / [[Small forward]]\n| height_m     = 2.03\n| weight_kg    = 90\n| league       = [[Liga ACB]]<br />[[EuroLeague]]\n| team         = Kirolbet Baskonia\n| number       = 33\n| nationality  = Italian\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1991|11|23}}\n| birth_place  = [[Ancona]], Italy\n| draft_year   = 2013\n| career_start = 2009\n| career_end   = \n| years1       = 2009\u20132012\n| team1        = [[Teramo Basket|Teramo]]\n| years2       = 2012\u20132014\n| team2        = [[Pallacanestro Varese|Varese]]\n| years3       = 2014\u20132017\n| team3        = [[Pallacanestro Reggiana|Reggiana]]\n| years4       = 2017\u20132019\n| team4        = [[Dinamo Sassari]]\n| years5       = 2019\u2013present\n| team5        = [[Saski Baskonia|Baskonia]]\n| highlights   = \n* [[FIBA Europe Cup]] champion ([[2018\u201319 FIBA Europe Cup|2019]])\n* [[Italian Basketball Supercup|Italian Supercup]] winner (2015)\n* 4\u00d7 [[Lega Basket All Star Game|Serie A All-Star]] (2012\u20132015)\n* [[Lega Basket All Star Game#Slam dunk contest|Serie A Slam Dunk Contest winner]] (2014)\n* 2\u00d7 [[Lega Basket Serie A awards#Best Player Under 22|Serie A Best Player Under 22]] (2012, 2013)\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Men's basketball}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Italy national basketball team|Italy]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2011 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|2011 Spain]]|}}\n}}\n'''Achille Polonara''' (born November 23, 1991) is an Italian professional [[basketball]] player for [[Saski Baskonia|Kirolbet Baskonia]] of the [[Liga ACB]] and the [[EuroLeague]]. He plays primarily as [[Power forward (basketball)|power forward]].\n\n==Professional career==\n===Teramo Basket===\nAfter progressing though the youth ranks of [[Teramo Basket|Banca Tercas Teramo]], Polonara debuted in the first division, the [[Lega Basket Serie A|Serie A]], on the first game of [[2009\u201310 Lega Basket Serie A|2009-10]] though he rarely featured that season and played sparingly the next.\n\nHe played more regularly during the [[2011\u201312 Lega Basket Serie A|2011-12 season]] with 8.2 points and 4,5 rebounds in 15.6 minutes on average, some coming from a stellar performance against [[Sutor Basket Montegranaro|Fabi Shoes Montegranaro]] in April with 34 points (13/14 from the field) and 9 rebounds for a [[Efficiency (basketball)|valuation]] of  46.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/basket/serie_a/2012/04/25-235635/Hairston+punisce+l'Acea,+Polonara+castiga+la+Fabi |title=Hairston punisce l'Acea, Polonara castiga la Fabi |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=25 April 2012 |website=[[Corriere dello Sport \u2013 Stadio]] |location=Roma |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Hairston punishes Acea, Polonara chastises Fabi |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304115230/http://www.corrieredellosport.it/basket/serie_a/2012/04/25-235635/Hairston+punisce+l'Acea,+Polonara+castiga+la+Fabi |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nThis helped the youngster win the [[Lega Basket Serie A awards#Best Player Under 22|Best Player Under 22]] award for the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Basket/Italia/10-05-2012/serie-a-mvp-bo-mccalebb-sacchetti-allenatore-anno-911188431137.shtml |title=Serie A, l'Mvp \u00e8 Bo McCalebb. Sacchetti allenatore dell'anno |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 May 2012 |website=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]] |location=Milan |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Serie A, the MVP is Bo McCalebb. Sacchetti coach of the year}}</ref>\nHe was also selected (as a replacement) for the Serie A All Star Game.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fip.it/news.asp?IDNews=4557 |title=Edison All Star Game 2012. Achille Polonara sostituisce Alessandro Gentile |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=7 March 2012 |website=[[Federazione Italiana Pallacanestro]] |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Edison All Star Game 2012. Achille Polonara replaces Alessandro Gentile}}</ref>\n\n===Cimberio Varese===\nTeramo was struggling financially and filed for bankruptcy during the summer of 2012, forcing Polonara to find a new club, which he did in July, signing a 3-year contract containing various escape clauses with [[Pallacanestro Varese|Cimberio Varese]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.laprovinciadivarese.it/stories/Homepage/303661_cimberio_la_squadra__fatta_oggi_colpo_finale_lesterno_usa/ |title=Cimberio, la squadra \u00e8 fatta. Oggi colpo finale: l'esterno Usa |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=24 July 2012 |website=La Provincia di Varese.it |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Cimberio, the squad is formed. Today the final piece: an American guard}}</ref>\nBoth parties profited from the deal as Polonara contributed 9.5 points, 5.4 rebounds and 1.6 steals in 23 minutes per game to help the side finish first in the [[2012\u201313 Lega Basket Serie A|2012-13 regular season]].\nHe posted 5.8 points, 3.4 rebounds and 0.8 steals in 15 minutes per game in the playoffs as Varese took eventual champions [[Mens Sana 1871 Basket|Montepaschi Siena]] to a seventh game in the [[2012\u201313 Lega Basket Serie A#Playoffs|semifinals]]. Polonara was named as the Best Player Under 22 for the second successive season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/coid_lWz,gzAEJtAxztLDoSo5D0.articleMode_on.html |title=Datome replicates Gallinari's feat |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=3 May 2013 |website=[[FIBA Europe]] |access-date=29 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe next season saw major players such as [[Bryant Dunston]] leave the side,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://milombardia.gazzetta.it/milano/2013-08-19/basket-primo-giorno-lavoro-varese-frates-milano-nettamente-favorita-20993532407.shtml |title=Basket, primo giorno di lavoro per Varese. Frates: \"Milano nettamente favorita\" |last=Cirelli |first=Matteo |date=19 August 2013 |website=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]] Milano |location=Milan |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Basketball: first workday for Varese. Frates: \"Milan by far the favourite\" |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702142057/http://milombardia.gazzetta.it/milano/2013-08-19/basket-primo-giorno-lavoro-varese-frates-milano-nettamente-favorita-20993532407.shtml |archive-date=2 July 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> which meant Polonara accrued more playing time.\nHowever, Varese had an anonymous season, losing to [[EWE Baskets Oldenburg|Oldenburg]] in the [[Euroleague 2013\u201314 qualifying rounds|Euroleague qualifying rounds]] despite Polonara's team high 18 points to exit Europe's premier competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.euroleague.net/main/results/showgame?gamecode=1&seasoncode=EQR13!report |title=2013-14 Qualifying Round 1: Cimberio Varese - EWE Baskets Oldenburg (Report) |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=1 October 2013 |website=[[Euroleague]] |access-date=23 May 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160122042217/http://www.euroleague.net/main/results/showgame?gamecode=1 |archive-date=22 January 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nDemoted to the European second tier [[EuroCup Basketball|EuroCup]], Varese finished last in [[Eurocup 2013\u201314 Regular Season Group C|group C]] to also exit the competition, with Polonara posting 7.2 points and 3.6 rebounds per game.<ref name=EurocupSigns>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/news/i/139766/achille-polonara-signs-with-reggio-emilia |title=Achille Polonara signs with Reggio Emilia |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=22 July 2014 |website=[[Eurocup Basketball]] |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref>\nThe team also finished out of playoff contention in the [[2013\u201314 Lega Basket Serie A|league]], though he had figures of 10.5 points and 4.8 rebounds per game. The [[Ancona]]n received a third successive call up to the All Star Game, played in his hometown, winning the Slam Dunk contest.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.laprovinciadivarese.it/stories/Sport/qui-credono-negli-italiani-varese-leale-umile-vera_1054637_11/ |title=Qui credono negli italiani. Varese leale, umile, vera |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=15 April 2014 |website=La Provincia di Varese.it |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Here they believe in Italians. Varese is loyal, humble and true}}</ref>\n\nVarese lost its main sponsor during the off-season, meaning that Polonara's reported \u20ac180,000 final contract year was too costly, he wasn't prepared to take a pay cut and wanted to play in a European competition to keep progressing so left the side.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gazzettadireggio.gelocal.it/sport/2014/07/11/news/basket-reggio-ha-in-pugno-polonara-1.9578205 |title=Basket, Reggio ha in pugno Polonara |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=11 July 2014 |website=[[Gazzetta di Reggio]] |location=Reggio Emilia |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Basketball, Reggio has Polonara in its hands}}</ref>\n\n===Pallacanestro Reggiana===\nPolonara joined [[Pallacanestro Reggiana|Grissin Bon Reggio Emilia]] in July 2014, signing a three-year contract (with a mutual escape clause after the second year) with the EuroCup playing side.<ref name=EurocupSigns /> He cited Reggio's practice of playing young Italians as a factor in the decision.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pallacanestroreggiana.it/4621/Triennale-per-Achille-Polonara |title=Triennale per Achile Polonara |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=22 July 2014 |website=[[Pallacanestro Reggiana]] |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Achille Polonara for three years}}</ref>\n\nThough Reggio were eliminated in the [[Eurocup 2014\u201315 Regular Season Group A|Eurocup group stage]], Polonara started all games, ending as the team's second best scorer (11ppg) and best rebounder (6.4rpg) for a team second 14.3 valuation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/competition/teams/showteam?clubcode=REG#!stats |title=Grissin Bon Reggio Emilia \u2013 Stats (2014-15) |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Eurocup Basketball]] |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref>\nHe even picked up a (shared) Round 7 MVP award after a determinant contribution to the November 2014 win over [[Levallois Metropolitans|Paris-Levallois]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/news/i/145934/regular-season-round-7-co-mvps-achille-polonara-grissin-bon-reggio-emilia-and-romeo-travis-krasny-oktyabr-volgograd |title=Regular Season Round 7 co-MVPs: Achille Polonara, Grissin Bon Reggio Emilia and Romeo Travis, Krasny Oktyabr Volgograd |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=27 November 2014 |website=[[Eurocup Basketball]] |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nPolonara had his breakout year in the Serie A, playing more minutes (31.1) than any other teammate, he also finished as second best scorer and best rebounder to earn the highest valuation of the team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pallacanestroreggiana.it/pagina.php?id=13&n=TEAM&year=2014 |title=Serie A, 2014/2015 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Pallacanestro Reggiana]] |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620062456/http://www.pallacanestroreggiana.it/pagina.php?id=13&n=TEAM&year=2014 |archivedate=20 June 2015 }}</ref> His figures of 8.4 rebounds and 18.1 in valuation per game also ranked him [[2014\u201315 Lega Basket Serie A#Individual Statistics.2C Regular Season|5th in the league]] for each, with [[La Gazzetta dello Sport|Gazzetta]] choosing him as their second most improved player for 2014-15.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Basket/12-05-2015/samuels-brooks-peric-vitali-ea7-milano-legabasket-umana-venezia-vanoli-cremona-110795255241.shtml |title=Basket, i premi Gazzetta: Samuels giocatore dell\u2019anno, poi Peric, Brooks e Vitali |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=12 May 2015 |website=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]] |location=Milan |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Basketball, the Gazzetta awards: Samuels player of the year before Peric, Brooks and Vitali}}</ref>\n\n===Baskonia===\nOn August 28, 2019, Polonara signed a two-year deal with [[Liga ACB|Spanish]] [[EuroLeague]] club [[Saski Baskonia|Kirolbet Baskonia]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Baskonia lands Polonara at frontcourt |url=https://www.euroleague.net/news/i/9wfx7omx44an4sxy |accessdate=28 August 2019 |work=EuroLeague.net |date=28 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nPolonara started playing for the youth squads of the [[Italy national basketball team|Italian national team]], first with the Under-18's at the [[2009 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|2009 European Championship]]. He notably won the silver medal with the U20's at the [[2011 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|2011 European Championship]] where he was an important contributor, including being the best performer in the semifinal against [[France national basketball team|France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/cid_KNce8jInH7Qj1EsyH5rjn2.gameID_8243-63-A-1.compID_UIfgjyQcGqk-fPlnl66Tj0.season_2011.roundID_8166.html |title=Under20 European Championship 2011: France - Italy |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=23 July 2011 |website=[[FIBA Europe]] |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nPolonara was called up to the preliminary squad of the senior team as a temporary replacement for the injured [[Nicol\u00f2 Melli]] as they prepared for [[EuroBasket 2013]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/cid_uDdn2ufWG9cE5xoT7qQLi2.coid_G0bjcraTIMg1iN8b7rnJs0.articleMode_on.html |title=Italy sweep at Trentino cup |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=28 July 2013 |website=[[FIBA Europe]] |access-date=29 June 2015}}</ref> However he himself later picked an ankle injury and was dropped from the squad.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/cid_3-I9xIK,H52ZNfYSgahgJ0.coid_6hlGORFNIHsCd,n5BZJ2r2.articleMode_on.html |title=Italy sweat over Bargnani health |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=7 August 2013 |website=[[FIBA Europe]] |access-date=29 June 2015}}</ref> \nHe would rejoin the senior side in 2014, scoring 20 points on his genuine (discounting the All Star Game) debut against [[Germany national basketball team|German]], he then became a regular in Italy squads.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fip.it/giocatori.asp?IDGiocatore=110&Tipo=M |title=Achille Polonara |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Federazione Italiana Pallacanestro]] |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nParticipating in the successful [[EuroBasket 2015 qualification#Group G|EuroBasket 2015 qualification]], he played in all 4 games with an average of 3.8 points and 1.3 rebounds in 8.5 minutes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurobasket2015.org/en/cid_FaTi64YyIbQDnvc3JDbil1.teamID_307.compID_qMRZdYCZI6EoANOrUf9le2.season_2015.roundID_9318.playerID_77353.html |title=Achille Polonara (Italy) |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[EuroBasket 2015]] |access-date=29 June 2015}}</ref>\nHe was called up to the squad that would take part in [[EuroBasket 2015]] to start on 5 September.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/season_2015.coid_s,Z8kZaZIlsLwQFktgGes0.articleMode_on.html |title=Italy take their dream roster to Berlin |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 September 2015 |website=[[FIBA Europe|FIBAEurope]].com |access-date=2 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Player profile==\nA left handed [[stretch four]], his athleticism is his primary strength. He's an explosive and energetic player,<ref name=Eurohopes>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurohopes.com/news/1768/scouting-the-draft-eligible-european-prospects-achille-polonara/ |title=Scouting the Draft-Eligible European Prospects: Achille Polonara |last1=Bortoluzzi |first1=Davide |last2=Neri |first2=Lorenzo |date=24 December 2012 |website=Eurohopes.com |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref> who's quick and has a great vertical leap, the latter of which has seen him colloquially nicknamed \u201cPolonAir\u201d.<ref name=PolonAir>{{cite web |url=http://gazzettadireggio.gelocal.it/sport/2015/05/13/news/polonair-ala-da-guerra-1.11417196 |title=\"Polonair\", ala da guerra |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=13 May 2015 |website=[[Gazzetta di Reggio]] |location=Reggio Emilia |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Polonair\", war forward}}</ref>\n\nRebounding is his statistical strength on both ends of the court,<ref name=DraftExpress>{{cite web |url=http://www.draftexpress.com/article/European-Roundup-Dominant-Donatas-3590/ |title=European Roundup: Dominant Donatas |last=Givony |first=Jonathan |date=3 December 2010 |website=DraftExpress.com |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref> using his instincts and speed to surprise opponents.\n\nIn attack he's tough to defend as he can operate on the perimeter, where he's able to beat bigger and slower defenders with a fast first-step or punish loose marking with his jump shot. His great wingspan makes him even more potent, whilst he's also effective and smooth on the floor where he can cover ground quickly.\nOn the defensive side, besides rebounding, he's a great shot blocker thanks to his good timing and balance and also a good [[pick and roll]] defender who can switch with the guards thanks to his lateral speed and wingspan.<ref name=Eurohopes /><ref name=DraftExpress />\n\nA mayor negative is his lanky frame,<ref name=DraftExpress /> it can see him struggle defending against inside players or muscular guards, in offense it also limits his post move when he's back to the basket, making him an imperfect fit for the [[Power forward (basketball)|4 position]].\nFor the [[Small forward|3 position]], he lacks safe ball-handling on the dribble and needs to develop his shooting options to be a better fit and develop from his [[Tweener (basketball)|Tweener]] status.<ref name=Eurohopes />\n\nHowever, he has regularly been noted for his work ethic and determination,<ref name=Eurohopes /><ref name=DraftExpress /> helping him improve year on year to add a solid three pointer and the ability to score in traffic to his offensive repertoire,<ref name=PolonAir /> for future development he identifies defensive concentration, 1vs.1 play, especially with the right hand, and better three point shooting as priorities.<ref name=GazzettaBig>{{cite web |url=http://gazzettadireggio.gelocal.it/sport/2015/05/13/news/voglio-la-grissin-bon-in-eurolega-fra-le-big-1.11417352 |title=Voglio la Grissin Bon in Eurolega fra le big |last=Pigozzi |first=Linda |date=13 May 2015 |website=[[Gazzetta di Reggio]] |location=Reggio Emilia |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=I want Grissin Bon in the Euroleague with the bigs}}</ref>\n\n==Personal==\nAchille credits his older brother Valerio, who has had a career in the Italian lower leagues, as inspiring him to become a basketball player, the brothers (separated in age by 7 years) are very close.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legapallacanestro.com/b/conosciamo-valerio-polonara |title=Conosciamo meglio Valerio Polonara |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=20 November 2014 |website=LegaPallacanestro.com |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Get to know Valerio Polonara better |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701160944/http://www.legapallacanestro.com/b/conosciamo-valerio-polonara |archivedate=1 July 2015 }}</ref>\n\nHis nephew, Michele Serpilli, also plays basketball, with the [[Victoria Libertas Pesaro|Pesaro]] youth teams, he reportedly is an admirer of Polonara.<ref name=GazzettaBig />\n\nHe cites [[Amedeo Della Valle]], [[Riccardo Cervi]], [[Giovanni Pini]] and Adam Pechacek as his closest teammates at Reggio Emilia.<ref name=GazzettaBig />\n\n==Career statistics==\nSources: EuroCup (2014,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/competition/players/showplayer?pcode=002084&seasoncode=U2013 |title=Polonara, Achille \u2013 2013-14 Statistics |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Eurocup Basketball]] |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref>  2015),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/competition/players/showplayer?pcode=002084&seasoncode=U2014 |title=Polonara, Achille \u2013 2014-15 Statistics |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Eurocup Basketball]] |access-date=23 May 2015}}</ref> Serie A<ref>{{cite web |url=http://195.56.77.208/player/pbd.phtml?ply=POL-ACH-91&from=1980&team=1258&type2=t&name_search=Polonara |title=Polonara Achille - Statistiche individuali |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Lega Basket Serie A]] |access-date=29 June 2015 |language=Italian |trans-title=Polonara Achille - Individual statistics}}</ref>\n\n===EuroCup===\n{{Euroleague player statistics legend}}\n{{Euroleague player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2013\u201314 Eurocup Basketball|2013\u201314]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|  [[Pallacanestro Varese|Cimberio Varese]]\n| '''10''' || '''10''' || 25.3 || 27.8 || '''31.8''' || 62.5 || 3.6 || 1.1 || 1.0 || 0.5 || 7.2 || 6.0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2014\u201315 Eurocup Basketball|2014\u201315